title: A proceeding in the harmonie of King Dauids harpe That is to say, an exposition of 13. psalmes of the princely prophet Dauid, from the 22. vnto the 35. psalme, being a portion of the psalmes expounded by the reuerend Doctor Victorinus Strigelius, professor in Diuinity in the Vniuersity of Lipsia in Germany. Translated out of Latin into English by Richard Robinson, citizen of London. Anno Christi 1591. Seene and allovved. ...
author: Strigel, Victorinus, 1524-1569.
publisher: By Iohn Wolfe [and J. Charlewood], and are to be sold at his shop ouer against the great South dore of Saint Paule,
